<h2 id="surface-reconstruction-from-point-clouds">Surface Reconstruction from Point Clouds</h2>

<p>Neural-Pull was used to reconstruct 3D surfaces from point clouds. Given a point cloud $\textbf{P}$, and in this case the condition $\textbf{c}$ was not used, the neural network was overfitted to the shape. After training, Neural-Pull becomes a neural representation for a shape in 3D, and it‚Äôs visualized by applying marching cubes to reconstruct the mesh surface. Below figures show the reconstruction results &amp; comparisons on different datasets.</p>

